metadata.title: Real Talk for Change - Boston Community Conversation

questions.question_text: What's your question about the future of Boston and your place in it?
questions.notes: Main opening question to gather participants' concerns about Boston's future

questions.question_text: Do you have a particular story or experience that brings you to ask that now?
questions.notes: Follow-up to get personal experiences behind employment concerns

questions.question_text: How would you put your question about the future of Boston?
questions.notes: Prompting participant to articulate their question clearly

questions.question_text: Do you have a particular experience on the bus?
questions.notes: Follow-up about safety experiences on public transportation

questions.question_text: Have you had experiences like that?
questions.notes: Follow-up about safety concerns for children

questions.question_text: Are there other things that you're hearing from each other that kind of resonate with you or sound familiar?
questions.notes: Encouraging cross-conversation and finding common themes

questions.question_text: Is there anything else that you heard that reminds you of something that happened to you?
questions.notes: Drawing out more personal connections to shared themes

questions.question_text: Is there anything else you want to share?
questions.notes: Closing question to capture any remaining thoughts
